"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637049","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>There are four independent faith schools in Oldham.</p><p>In relation to encouraging community cohesion and integration in such schools, I refer to my previous Answer (52486); the position is the same for all independent schools.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T14:06:53.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637049/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637049/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Faith Schools: Oldham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 14 November 2016 to Question 52486, what estimate she has made of the number of independent faith schools in Oldham; and what steps her Department is taking to encourage community cohesion and integration in such schools.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","53102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637050","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>School playing fields are protected by Section 77 of the School Standards and Framework Act 1998. Schools and local authorities must obtain the Secretary of State’s approval before they can dispose of their land. Applications to dispose of school playing fields are considered by the school playing fields advisory panel, and are approved only when it is demonstrated that the application meets published criteria. I am aware of an application by Wirral Metropolitan Borough Council to seek approval to dispose of part of the playing fields at the closed Rock Ferry High School. The application is currently being processed by officials at the Education Funding Agency, who have sought further detail from the council about the proposal. The application can only be considered when sufficient information is available to enable the panel and the Secretary of State to assess where the capital receipt of the sale of the land will be spent and whether a local Residents’ Association will manage the remaining field for local use. The Secretary of State will consider the recommendation of the panel before making her final decision.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-11-22T14:09:20.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637050/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637050/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Rock Ferry School","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the timetable is for a decision to be taken on the future of the Rock Ferry High School site.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","53051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637051","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>We want to continue to attract and retain good quality staff to deliver good quality early years provision and the Government has committed to developing a workforce strategy to help employers to do this.</p><p>We are currently consulting on the English and mathematics knowledge, skills and qualification requirements for level 3 early years educator staff. We want the workforce strategy to reflect the government response to this consultation which closes on 28<sup>th</sup> November. We have already received a high volume of replies and it will take time to analyse and consider those responses.</p><p> </p><p>Development of the early years workforce strategy is a priority and we will publish as soon as possible.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T16:13:19.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637051/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637051/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Pre-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will set a publication date for the Early Years Workforce strategy.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","53105"
