"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637054","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>We want to continue to attract and retain good quality staff to deliver good quality early years provision and the Government has committed to developing a workforce strategy to help employers to do this.</p><p>We are currently consulting on the English and mathematics knowledge, skills and qualification requirements for level 3 early years educator staff. We want the workforce strategy to reflect the government response to this consultation which closes on 28<sup>th</sup> November. We have already received a high volume of replies and it will take time to analyse and consider those responses.</p><p> </p><p>Development of the early years workforce strategy is a priority and we will publish as soon as possible.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T16:30:35.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637054/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637054/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Pre-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans for the Early Years Workforce Strategy to be published.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","52970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637055","Department for Education","false","2016-11-18","<p>The quality ratings for childcare providers continue to rise and the latest figures show that 91% of providers on the Early Years Register achieved a “good” or “outstanding” rating as at 31 August 2016 – the highest proportion ever.</p><p>Ofsted is the non-ministerial government department responsible for the regulation of childcare providers and publishes a regular series of statistics on provider numbers and inspection outcomes on their website, including those specifically requested in this question. These can be viewed from the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-years-and-childcare-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-years-and-childcare-statistics</a>.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","53025 ; 53028","2016-11-18T11:28:30.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637055/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637055/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Ofsted-registered childcare providers have been inspected by Ofsted in the last (a) one, (b) two, (c) three and (d) four years.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","53024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637056","Department for Education","false","2016-11-18","<p>The quality ratings for childcare providers continue to rise and the latest figures show that 91% of providers on the Early Years Register achieved a “good” or “outstanding” rating as at 31 August 2016 – the highest proportion ever.</p><p>Ofsted is the non-ministerial government department responsible for the regulation of childcare providers and publishes a regular series of statistics on provider numbers and inspection outcomes on their website, including those specifically requested in this question. These can be viewed from the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-years-and-childcare-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-years-and-childcare-statistics</a>.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","53024 ; 53028","2016-11-18T11:28:30.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637056/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637056/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Ofsted-registered childcare providers there were in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","53025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637057","Department for Education","false","2016-11-18","<p>Ofsted is the non-ministerial government department responsible for the regulation of childcare providers in England. Ofsted is responsible for considering and responding to information notified to them by providers and for taking subsequent enforcement action where appropriate. We have informed Ofsted of this question and Her Majesty's Chief Inspector will be writing to the hon. Member in response. A copy of that letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-18T11:27:12.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637057/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637057/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637057/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many inspections have been carried out by Ofsted arising from information given to Ofsted by managers of childcare providers in each year since 2010; and how many providers have lost their registration as a result of inspections arising from such information.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","53027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637058","Department for Education","false","2016-11-18","<p>The quality ratings for childcare providers continue to rise and the latest figures show that 91% of providers on the Early Years Register achieved a “good” or “outstanding” rating as at 31 August 2016 – the highest proportion ever.</p><p>Ofsted is the non-ministerial government department responsible for the regulation of childcare providers and publishes a regular series of statistics on provider numbers and inspection outcomes on their website, including those specifically requested in this question. These can be viewed from the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-years-and-childcare-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-years-and-childcare-statistics</a>.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","53024 ; 53025","2016-11-18T11:28:30.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637058/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637058/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Ofsted-registered childcare providers were rated (a) outstanding, (b) good, (c) satisfactory and (d) inadequate in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","53028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637059","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>The Government is committed to extending the entitlement to childcare from 15 to 30 hours a week for working parents of three- and four-year-olds. We are clear that we need to get the funding right to ensure that providers are funded on a fair and sustainable basis. We will be investing over £1billion more per year by 2019-20 to fund our commitments on the early years entitlements – this includes £300 million per year from 2017-18 for a significant increase to the hourly rate paid for the two-, three- and four-year-old entitlements.</p><p> </p><p>Our recent consultation set out proposals to allocate our record level of funding fairly and transparently, with the maximum amount reaching providers. We will publish our response shortly.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T16:07:43.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637059/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637059/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether additional support will be available for providers who are negatively financially impacted as a result of the introduction of 30 hours of free childcare policy.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","52964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637060","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>The Government will be investing over £1billion more per year by 2019-20 to fund our commitments on the early years entitlements – this includes £300 million per year from 2017-18 for a significant increase to the hourly rate paid for the two-, three- and four-year-old entitlements.</p><p> </p><p>It is vital that funding for these entitlements is fairly distributed between different parts of the country and different types of providers, so that they can deliver both the existing 15-hour entitlement and the extended 30-hour entitlement for working parents, on a sustainable basis.</p><p> </p><p>That is why we have recently consulted on our proposals for a national funding formula for the early years. Under our proposals, 75% of local authorities would have higher funding rates, and providers in the vast majority of local authorities can expect to gain funding, as maximum funding is passed through to the frontline. We are currently considering all responses to the consultation, and are planning to publish the government’s response shortly.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T16:13:53.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637060/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637060/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to ensure that providers receive the adequate level of funding to deliver the 30 hours of free childcare policy.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","52965"
