"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637077","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-18","<p>The increase in the maximum sentences only came into effect on 1 August 2016. No such assessments have therefore been made.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-18T09:34:34.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637077/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637077/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Animal Welfare: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the deterrent effect that increased maximum sentences for cruelty against animals have had in Northern Ireland; and whether she has made an assessment of the implications of those effects for her Department's policies.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","52929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637078","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-18","<p>The consultation on reducing emissions from Medium Combustion Plants and Generators to improve air quality was published on 16 November this year and runs for 12 weeks. The proposals can be found on the GOV.UK web pages.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-18T10:52:41.96Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637078/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637078/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Diesel Engines: Nitrogen Oxides","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the timetable is for publication of her Department's proposed consultation on Proposals to regulate generators with high NOx emissions; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","52901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637079","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-18","<p>Defra does not hold data on local authority Trading Standards inspections of animals during transit for slaughter abroad. APHA carry out supervised loadings on export consignments of live animals for slaughter.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-18T14:39:38.283Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637079/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637079/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Livestock: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many inspections Trading Standards has undertaken of animals during transit for slaughter abroad in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Williams","Ceredigion","Mr Mark Williams","52956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637080","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-22","<p>There are no proposals to introduce a licensing regime for cat breeding. The only licensing regime for animal breeding relates to dog breeding and this is because of past concerns about the welfare conditions at some such breeding establishments. Local authorities have powers under the Animal Welfare Act 2006 to investigate any concerns about the welfare standards at cat breeding establishments.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-22T15:02:46.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637080/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637080/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Cats: Animal Breeding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she made of the potential merits of the regulation of commercial cat breeding to improve safeguards for cat welfare through the introduction of cat breeding licensing, welfare conditions and standards and an inspection process.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","52969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637081","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-23","<p>The number of working days lost in Defra due to mental illness in the last three years is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June to July 2013/14</p></td><td><p>1519.40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June to July 2014/15</p></td><td><p>1966.91</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June to July 2015/16</p></td><td><p>2374.62</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-23T15:26:58.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637081/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637081/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many working days were lost due to mental illness in her Department in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","53068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637082","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-18","<p>National Statistics on bovine TB, which include new herd incidents, are published monthly on gov.uk and can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/incidence-of-tuberculosis-tb-in-cattle-in-great-britain" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/incidence-of-tuberculosis-tb-in-cattle-in-great-britain</a>.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-18T09:50:21.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637082/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637082/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Bovine Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many new incidents of bovine TB there have been in each month in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","53162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637083","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-18","<p>Information on the total application of nitrogen, phosphate, potash and sulphur on farmland across the UK in each of the last five years is not available. However, the average application of those same nutrients on Great British farmland in each of the last five years is collected in the British Survey of Fertiliser Practice.</p><p> </p><p>This annual survey collects data on fertiliser and manure use in Great Britain. From these, annual reports are produced on fertiliser use in Great Britain which provide figures dating back to 1983 and in-depth analysis. The latest report from 2015 can be found on the Government’s website at GOV.UK.</p><p> </p><p>The table below summarises data from the British Survey of Fertiliser Practice on application rates of nitrogen, phosphate, potash, and sulphur in Great Britain from 2011 to 2015 for all crops and grass combined. Information regarding nutrient application to farmland in Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Northern Ireland Office.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Nitrogen (kg/ha)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Phosphate (kg/ha)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Potash (kg/ha)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Sulphur (kg/ha)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>99</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>95</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>94</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>99</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>98</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-18T09:44:33.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637083/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637083/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-15","Agriculture: Fertilisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate she has made of the total application of (a) nitrogen, (b) phosphate, (c) potash and (d) sulphur on farmland across the UK in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","53157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637084","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>US immigration policy is a matter for the US.</p><p>I note that US Customs and Border Protection states that &quot;the religion, faith, or spiritual beliefs of an international traveller are not determining factors about his/her admissibility into the US&quot;.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-23T15:19:17.94Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637084/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637084/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","USA: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to ensure that British Muslims wishing to travel to the US can do so within normal terms applied to non-Muslims and not prescribed by the comments of President-Elect Trump on 7 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","53148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637085","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Danish authorities are conducting further enquiries as part of their investigation. We understand that they aim to conclude this by the middle of January 2017. Consular staff remain in contact with the Danish authorities and Mr O’Malley’s family.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-18T14:32:16.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637085/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637085/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Stephen O'Malley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 29 June 2016 to Question 41097, what further information he has on the progress being made by the Danish authorities on the re-opened inquest into the death of Stephen O'Malley; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","53163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637086","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>Ambassadors and High Commissioners have raised Female Genital Mutilation (FGM) with the governments of Chad, Cameroon, Eritrea, Gambia, Ghana, Guinea, Liberia, Mali, Mauritania, Senegal, Sierra Leone, Somalia, Sudan, Tanzania and Uganda. The Secretary of State for International Development raised it with the President of Sierra Leone during her visit earlier in November. The UK does not shy away from raising FGM with governments as part of our wider human rights dialogue.</p><p>The UK is committed to working with governments and international and local partners to eradicate the abusive practice of female genital mutilation. Our ongoing commitment is demonstrated through the 2014 UK-hosted Girl Summit, our flagship £35 million regional programme and bilateral work in many countries.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","52971 ; 52993 ; 52994 ; 52995 ; 52996 ; 52997 ; 52998 ; 52999 ; 53252 ; 53253 ; 53254 ; 53255 ; 53256 ; 53257 ; 53258 ; 53259 ; 53260 ; 53261 ; 53262 ; 53263 ; 53264 ; 53266 ; 53267 ; 53268 ; 53269 ; 53295 ; 53496 ; 53497","2016-11-23T17:12:27.847Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637086/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637086/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Egypt: Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the UK ambassador to Egypt has made representations to the government of Egypt on the practice of female genital mutilation.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","53152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637087","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>​We are not aware of any human rights complaints or allegations relating to BP's Bintuni Bay operation. BP is a member of the UN Global Compact and has an extensive Corporate Social Responsibility programme in Papua that supports education, healthcare and economic development in the local community. The British Ambassador to Indonesia has personally visited BP's Tangguh project and a village in Bintuni Bay to discuss the impact of BP operations and their community development programs in the region.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-11-23T15:43:00.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637087/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637087/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Indonesia: British Petroleum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that BP operations in the Bintuni Bay area in West Papua recently authorised by the Indonesian government are undertaken in accordance with (a) UK and international human rights law and (b) the OECD Guidelines for Multinational Enterprises.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","53120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637088","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>​The number of working days lost due to mental illness in the last three years (1st April to 31st March) was as follows:-</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td>Working days lost</td></tr><tr><td>2015/16</td><td>909</td></tr><tr><td>2014/15</td><td>712</td></tr><tr><td>2013/14</td><td>393</td></tr></tbody></table>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-23T15:30:27.04Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637088/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637088/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many working days were lost due to mental illness in his Department in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","53069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637089","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-18","<p>​We will continue to raise our grave concerns about Israeli settlements with the Israeli Government. On 16 November I issued a public statement expressing our deep concern over the land regulation bill in the Israeli Knesset which seeks to ‘legalise’ settlement outposts across the West Bank. Such outposts are currently illegal under both Israeli domestic law and international humanitarian law. Should this proposal go ahead, it would seriously undermine prospects for a two-state solution. We urge the Israeli Government to reconsider the land regulation bill at the earliest opportunity. On 3 November I also issued a public statement condemning the recent announcement by the Israeli authorities to approve permits for constructing 181 new homes in the illegal settlement of Gilo in East Jerusalem. Our Embassy in Tel Aviv have also regularly raised our concerns with the Israeli authorities on the continued expansion of settlements and the retroactive &quot;legalisation&quot; of outposts in the West Bank.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-18T14:47:53.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637089/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637089/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Occupied Territories: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to discourage illegal settlements in Palestine.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","53030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637090","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>​The British Ambassador to Indonesia regularly discusses both human rights and economic development in the Indonesian provinces of West Papua and Papua with the Indonesian government. We will continue to make representations about historical cases and highlight any human rights concerns.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-11-23T15:45:12.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637090/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637090/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Indonesia: Demonstrations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to the Indonesian government on the reported arrest and detention of protestors this summer in West Papua.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","53007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637091","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Government is deeply concerned by the reports of mass killings in Beni. During my visit to the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) in August, I raised the ongoing violence in eastern DRC with Maman Sidikou, Head of the UN Peacekeeping Mission in eastern DRC (MONUSCO). In addition, our Ambassador to the Democratic Republic of the Congo, regularly discusses the Beni situation with the MONUSCO leadership and the DRC Government. The EU Foreign Affairs Council Conclusions of 17 October reiterated the EU’s profound concern at the situation in Beni and reminded all involved of the UN sanctions regime for those responsible for serious human rights violations. Most recently, our representative on the UNSC visited eastern DRC last week to explore what more MONUSCO can do to prevent future killings.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-23T16:53:16.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637091/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637091/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Democratic Republic of Congo: Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his international counterparts on reports of recent massacres in Beni and the North Kivu region in the Democratic Republic of Congo.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","53002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637092","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Global Coalition continues to coordinate closely as we reach a key phase of the campaign against Daesh. All five of the Coalition's Working Groups have met in the last two months, including Communications which I co-chaired. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, My Right Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson) and the Secretary of State for Defence, my Right Hon. Friend the Member for Sevenoaks (Sir Michael Fallon), attended meetings in Paris in October shortly after the operation to take Mosul began. Most recently, the Small Group of Coalition senior officials met in Berlin on 17 November.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-23T16:59:44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637092/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637092/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his international counterparts on improving diplomatic co-ordination against Daesh.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","53003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637093","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>​Decisions on appointments to the Indonesian President's cabinet are a matter for the Indonesian President.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-11-23T15:51:30.08Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637093/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637093/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Indonesia: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will raise with his counterpart in Indonesia the appointment of General Wiranto as that country's security minister.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","53004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637094","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-21","<p>As the UK leaves the European Union, the Government intends to strengthen its bilateral relationships with countries in Europe and around the world.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-21T15:42:09.113Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637094/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637094/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the UK's decision to leave the EU on UK bilateral relations with (a) other EU and (b) non-EU countries.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","53005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637095","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-18","<p>While we have not raised this specific point, I raised the wider issue of Palestinian minors in detention with the Israeli Ambassador to London on 10 November. The treatment of Palestinian children in Israeli military detention remains a human rights priority for the UK. We have expressed our concerns to the Israeli authorities on the use of single hand ties and the need to notify children of their legal rights. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv most recently raised the issue of Palestinian children in detention with the Israeli authorities on 10 October. We remain committed to working with the Israeli authorities to encourage further changes in practice.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-18T14:51:32.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637095/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637095/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Israel: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Israeli government on the overnight detention of Palestinian minors.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","53046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637096","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-18","<p>The UK will recognise a Palestinian state at a time most helpful to the peace process. We judge that a negotiated end to the occupation is the most effective way for Palestinian aspirations of statehood to be met. We continue to be one of the principal supporters of Palestinian state building efforts, assisting them to tackle poverty, build institutions and boost their economy.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-18T14:49:24.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637096/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637096/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Palestinians: Recognition of States","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what criteria the Government uses in order to assess whether the recognition of Palestinian statehood would be conducive to peace in that region.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","53047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637097","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-18","<p>I refer the hon Member for Brentford and Isleworth to the answer I gave to the hon Member for East Ham today, UIN 53031.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2016-11-18T12:38:43.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637097/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637097/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-15","West Bank: Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether public bodies are covered by the advice on the UK Trade and Investment website not to trade with illegal settlements in the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","53026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637098","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>I met the Scottish Government Minister for UK Negotiations on Scotland's Place in Europe in the context of the Joint Ministerial Council (Europe Negotiations) on 9 November<em>.</em> The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson) has not yet met any Minister in the Scottish Government in his official capacity, but is committed to do so as part of the FCO's continued engagement and cooperation with each of the Devolved Administrations.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-23T15:16:15.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637098/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637098/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-15","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many times he has met Ministers of the Scottish Government since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","53001"
