"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637235","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-23","<p>Energy supply companies must ensure that all domestic customers are on the cheapest tariff that is in line with their preferences: that is in relation to their chosen payment method and whether they prefer a fixed term or variable tariff.</p><p>Eligible vulnerable consumers, including cancer patients on Pension Credit Guarantee Credit or other means tested benefits, can receive help with energy bills through the Warm Home Discount.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-23T11:14:29.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637235/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637235/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will take steps to ensure that energy consumers with cancer are protected by a price cap.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","53114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637236","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>The operation and franchising of its Crown post offices is the responsibility of Post Office Limited.</p><p> </p><p>I have asked Paula Vennells, the Chief Executive of Post Office Limited, to write to the Hon Member on this matter and provide the information requested. A copy of her reply will be placed in the libraries of the House.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","53052 ; 53053 ; 53054","2016-11-18T13:19:27.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637236/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637236/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Post Offices: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many responses the Post Office has received to its consultation on proposals to franchise Crown post office branches since January 2014; and how many of those responses were opposed to those proposals.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","53056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637237","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>There is no set timetable for the publication of the annual Post Office Network report each year. Pursuant to section 11(6) of the Postal Services Act 2011, my Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State expects to lay the 2015/16 report in Parliament shortly. Once laid the Post Office will publish the report on its website.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-18T13:24:16.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637237/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637237/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Post Offices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the timetable is for the publication of the Post Office Network Report for 2016 pursuant to section 11 of the Postal Services Act 2011.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","53055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637238","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>The operation and franchising of its Crown post offices is the responsibility of Post Office Limited.</p><p> </p><p>I have asked Paula Vennells, the Chief Executive of Post Office Limited, to write to the Hon Member on this matter and provide the information requested. A copy of her reply will be placed in the libraries of the House.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","53052 ; 53053 ; 53056","2016-11-18T13:19:27.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637238/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637238/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Post Offices: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many Crown post offices which the Post Office is proposing to franchise in 2016 are in (a) urban deprived, (b) urban and (c) rural areas.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","53054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637239","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-21","<p>The Department supports the establishment of all businesses including cooperatives. Support for people wanting to start or grow their business is available from our Business Support Helpline, while 39 growth hubs in England bring together local business support so that local people can access it easily. British Business Bank programmes are improving access to finance, including Start-Up Loans which provide start up finance and business advice.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-21T10:54:37.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637239/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637239/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Cooperatives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what support his Department makes available for the establishment of new cooperatives in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","53104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637240","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Competition Market Authority has recently consulted on a draft order which set out the technical details of how the safeguard tariff cap for prepayment meters will be calculated and implemented. The consultation closed on 11 November, and the tariff cap is expected to come into force in April next year.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-23T16:41:03.99Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637240/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637240/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent progress has been made on introducing a cap on the cost of energy supplied through prepayment meters.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","53119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637241","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Government published its response accepting all the Low Pay Commission’s rate recommendations on 14 March 2016.</p><p>The Government is considering the Low Pay Commission’s non-rate recommendations. On the recommendation relating to a formal public protocol to handle third party whistleblowing on breaches of the National Minimum Wage, a trial is underway involving Citizens Advice Bureaux acting as a third party on behalf of complainants. The trial will be evaluated before a decision is taken on any wider roll-out.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-18T10:49:22.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637241/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637241/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Low Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he plans to respond to the recommendations by the Low Pay Commission made in the National Minimum Wage: Low Pay Commission Report, Spring 2016, published in March 2016.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","53165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637242","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Non-Financial Reporting Directive<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup> will be brought into force by The Companies, Partnerships and Groups (Accounts and Non-Financial Reporting) Regulations 2016 in time for the financial year commencing on or after 1 January 2017. The Regulations were laid in both Houses on 7 November 2016. Transposition will meet the minimum requirements of the Directive which is the Government’s preferred approach to EU implementation.</p><p>The implementation of the Regulations will be supported by the Financial Reporting Council’s Guidance on the Strategic Report and guidance from the Financial Conduct Authority. Further detail on the transposition of the Directive is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/non-financial-reporting-directive-uk-implementation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/non-financial-reporting-directive-uk-implementation</a></p><p> </p><p>[1] Directive 2014/95/EU on disclosure of non-financial and diversity information by certain large undertakings and groups.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-18T10:50:11.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637242/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637242/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Accountancy: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans he has to transpose the EU Non-Financial Reporting Directive into UK Law.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","53038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637243","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-22","<p>The Government has put in place a range of measures to support energy intensive industries (EIIs). This includes a package of compensation and exemption measures to alleviate the impact of renewable and low carbon policy costs passed through in electricity bills. By 2020, this package will reduce the impact of policies on the most energy intensive businesses’ energy bills by 80%.</p><p>Since 2014 the Government has exempted mineralogical and metallurgical processes from the Climate Change Levy (CCL) which is an energy consumption tax and other EIIs receive a significant discount from the CCL in exchange for signing up to energy efficiency or carbon reduction targets through Climate Change Agreements. Energy intensive sectors subject to the EU Emissions Trading System are allocated allowances for free to protect against the risk of carbon leakage. The Government is also working in collaboration with eight energy intensive sectors to develop action plans to support energy efficiency and decarbonisation measures while improving competitiveness.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-11-22T16:06:43.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637243/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637243/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Energy Intensive Industries: Trade Competitiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what support his Department provides to energy-intensive users in the manufacturing and engineering sectors.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","53009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637244","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>This government has a range of policies to improve the energy efficiency of non-domestic premises including policies to ensure organisations understand their energy use and how they can save money on their energy bills. Such policies include the Energy Savings Opportunity Scheme, incentives to invest in energy efficient technologies such as Enhanced Capital Allowances, access to finance for public sector buildings through Salix and the use of minimum standards for new and refurbished non-domestic buildings and those in the private rented sector.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-18T14:02:47.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637244/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637244/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Business Premises: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans his Department has to improve the energy efficiency of non-domestic premises.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","53034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637245","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-21","<p>The total number of working days lost due mental illness in each of the last 3 years for the Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy’s predecessors (the Department of Energy and Climate Change and the Department of Business, Industry and Strategy) are:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Period</p></td><td><p>Days Lost</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July to June 2013/14</p></td><td><p>3531</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July to June 2014/15</p></td><td><p>3199</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July to June 2015/16</p></td><td><p>3674</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Figures include only core departments with the 2013/14 figures including what is now the Oil and Gas Authority which became an Agency from 2014/15 and is excluded thereafter.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-21T10:47:53.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637245/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637245/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many working days were lost due to mental illness in his Department and its predecessor in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","53006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637246","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-21","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy has allocated £366m to the Economic and Social Research Council (ESRC) to spend on excellent research in the social sciences between April 2016 and March 2018. All Research Councils abide by the Haldane principle; how they spend their allocated funding is decided independently by ESRC’s council. The full programme expenditure for The UK in a Changing Europe currently stands at £4.95m; the programme began in 2014 and is scheduled to continue until December 2017.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-11-21T12:56:06.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637246/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637246/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Research: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how much he plans for his Department to contribute towards the Economic and Social Research Council grant programme, UK in a Changing Europe.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","53082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637247","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-18","<p>The operation and franchising of its Crown post offices is the responsibility of Post Office Limited.</p><p> </p><p>I have asked Paula Vennells, the Chief Executive of Post Office Limited, to write to the Hon Member on this matter and provide the information requested. A copy of her reply will be placed in the libraries of the House.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","53053 ; 53054 ; 53056","2016-11-18T13:19:27.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637247/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637247/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-15","Post Offices: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how much has been spent since January 2010 from the public purse on refurbishment of Crown post offices which are proposed to be franchised in July 2016.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","53052"
