"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636174","Department for Education","false","2016-11-18","<p>Ministers regularly meet with stakeholders, including representatives of the Russell Group, to discuss issues of interest to the sector.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-11-18T15:53:42.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636174/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636174/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-14","Russell Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she last met representatives of the Russell Group of universities; and what subjects were discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","52795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636175","Department for Education","false","2016-11-22","<p>Parents want good schools for their children and we know the vast majority of faith schools provide a high standard of education. The department wants to increase the number of good school places available, including at faith schools, and that’s why we are consulting on the proposals in “Schools that work for everyone” consultation document. We will consider evidence submitted alongside responses to the consultation.</p><p>The consultation document is available at: <a href="https://consult.education.gov.uk/school-frameworks/schools-that-work-for-everyone" target="_blank">https://consult.education.gov.uk/school-frameworks/schools-that-work-for-everyone</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T14:06:00.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636175/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636175/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-14","Faith Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of the implications for her policy on faith schools of (a) the Populus Poll commissioned by the Accord Coalition, published on 2 November 2016 and (b) the 2011 research paper entitled Faith Primary Schools: Better Schools or Better Pupils, written by Steve Gibbons and Olmo Silva.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","52815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636176","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-17","<p>The Government published a breakdown of employers in scope of the apprenticeship levy in August 2016. This suggested that 2,590 employers would be in the education sector. The full publication is available at<em>: </em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/545145/Apprenticeships_-expected_levy_and_total_spend_-_Aug_2016.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/545145/Apprenticeships_-expected_levy_and_total_spend_-_Aug_2016.pdf</a></p><p><em> </em></p><p>It is not possible to accurately identify the number of primary and secondary schools who will pay the levy because, for many, the employer will be a local council or multi academy trust.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-17T17:35:52.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636176/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636176/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-14","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) primary and (b) secondary schools will be obliged to pay the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","52832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636177","Home Office","false","2016-11-22","<p>The Tier 4 visa pilot scheme is designed to test the benefits of a differentiated approach within Tier 4, whilst ensuring any changes do not undermine the robust application of immigration requirements. No estimate has been made of financial benefits to the participating institutions. The results of the pilot will be carefully monitored to determine whether the scheme should be rolled out more widely. We will carefully monitor any impacts and liaise with stakeholders before any further steps are taken.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-22T17:27:06.69Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636177/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636177/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-14","Visas: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the potential financial benefits to universities involved in the introduction of the Tier 4 visa pilot scheme.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","52798"
